name: Chautauqua
description: The most famous scrambles in Boulder including the First, Second, and Third Flatirons.
parking: Chautauqua parking lot. Often full and paid from Memorial Day to Labor Day. Can fall back to street parking if lot is full.

scrambles.name: Freeway, Second Flatiron
scrambles.approachDescription: From the Chautauqua Ranger Cottage, take the Chautauqua Trail to the Flatirons Loop Trail. Follow it for about 0.2 miles, then turn onto the Second/Third Flatiron Trail. This leads straight to the base of the north side of the Second Flatiron. The hike takes around 30 minutes.
scrambles.scrambleDescription:
Start by working through a slight bulge with a crack—this is the first crux. From there, follow the path of least resistance by trending slightly right, then back left toward a gully. Use the available holds and step right onto the rib, aiming for an obvious tree ahead. Continue climbing up and slightly right over easier terrain.

You’ll soon see the Pullman Car formation looming to your left. Eventually, you’ll reach a small summit with a notch separating you from the rest of the route. Take the leap across—it’s easier than it looks!
scrambles.descentDescription: Step off the rock onto the trail between the First and Second Flatirons and follow it back down.
